name: Eggplant Tacos
author: DnDCross
summary: This is a fun, healthy recipe to change up your Mexican meals. Bet you almost can't tell that there isn't meat! Use as substitute for meat in tacos, enchiladas, or your favorite Mexican meals. Fill taco shells with eggplant mixture and top with your favorite fixings!
ingredients: ½ teaspoon seasoned salt (such as Johnny's Seasoning Salt®)
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat
Stir onion, lemon juice, garlic, and jalapeno pepper into skillet; bring to a simmer and cook until onions soften, about 3 minutes
Stir eggplant, cumin, paprika, chili powder, black pepper, and seasoned salt into onion mixture; drizzle remaining olive oil over the top
Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggplant reduces in size and softens, about 15 minutes
Spoon eggplant mixture into tortilla shells
